article.description: — Lamar Wilkerson scored 25 points as Sam Houston beat New Mexico State 79-58 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Wilkerson's 25 help Sam Houston defeat New Mexico State 79-58
article.linkText: Wilkerson's 25 help Sam Houston defeat New Mexico State 79-58
article.story: LAS CRUCES, N.M. -- — Lamar Wilkerson scored 25 points as Sam Houston beat New Mexico State 79-58 on Thursday night. Wilkerson was 8 of 12 shooting (7 for 8 from 3-point range) for the Bearkats (16-11, 9-3 Conference USA). Marcus Boykin was 3 of 8 shooting and 6 of 10 from the free throw line to add 13 points. Davon Barnes went 4 of 5 from the field to finish with 12 points. The Aggies (11-16, 5-7) were led in scoring by Kaosi Ezeagu, who finished with 15 points, seven rebounds and two blocks. Christian Cook added 14 points for New Mexico State. NEXT UP Both teams next play Saturday. Sam Houston visits UTEP and New Mexico State plays Louisiana Tech at home. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
